==English==
===Etymology===
Old English [[Sæternesdæg]] ("day of the planet Saturn") < [[Sætern]] ("Saturn") < Latin [[Saturnus]] (god of agriculture, possibly from Etruscan) + Old English [[dæg]] ("day"). A calque on [[dies Saturni]]. See [[day]].

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-Saturday.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''Saturday'''

#The sixth day of the week in Europe and in systems using the ISO 8601 norm.
#The seventh [[day]] of the [[week]] in the USA.
#The Biblical seventh [[day]] of the [[week]], observed as [[Sabbath]] or "Day of Rest". It follows [[Friday]] and precedes [[Sunday]].
#An appointment, person, or feeling associated with this day of the week.

